The catalog level number column indicates the level of the product in the catalog hierarchy. The parent entry id column indicates the id of the parent product in the catalog hierarchy. The previous entry id column indicates the id of the previous product in the catalog hierarchy. The next entry id column indicates the id of the next product in the catalog hierarchy. The catalog entry name column stores the name of the product. The product stock number column indicates the stock number of the product. The price in dollars column indicates the price of the product in US dollars. The price in euros column indicates the price of the product in euros. The price in pounds column indicates the price of the product in British pounds. The capacity column indicates the capacity of the product. The length column indicates the length of the product. The height column indicates the height of the product. The width column indicates the width of the product.

This table stores additional attributes for catalog entries. The catalog entry id column is a foreign key to the catalog entries table. The catalog level number column indicates the level of the catalog entry in the catalog hierarchy. The attribute id column is a foreign key to the attributes table. The attribute value column stores the value of the attribute for the catalog entry.
